<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-05T12:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-05T12:36:00-05:00" n="1039" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1039">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/958</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Querétaro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-05T11:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 5, 1916, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s December 28, 11 a.m. Mining taxes. Subsecretary informed me
                            this morning Chief Executive is disposed to reconsider and reform
                            present mining decree granting interests a considerable reduction. He
                            awaits the arrival here of Cabrera in order to finally formulate the
                            modifications.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>